Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of smart antenna systems in cellular networks to enhance spectral density and reduce power consumption and RF pollution, which falls under the domain of network infrastructure and wireless communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also mentions demand-based frequency allocation techniques, which falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT). The use of smart antenna systems also involves signal processing (cs.MM) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper proposes a new cellular network design for Indian conditions, which falls under the domain of computer engineering (cs.CE).
